    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1968-05-09T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1968-05-09T13:00:00-05:00" n="198"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d198">
                <head>198. Action Memorandum From the President’s Special Assistant (<persName
                        corresp="#p_RWW1" type="from">Rostow</persName>) to President <persName
                        corresp="#p_JUA1" type="to">Johnson</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d198fn1">Source: Johnson Library, National
                        Security File, Country File, Korea, Memos, Vol. VI. No classification
                        marking.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1968-05-09T14:00:00-04:00">May 9, 1968, 2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Loan to the Korean Reconstruction Bank</item>
                </list>
                <p>Attached is a Zwick-Gaud<note n="2" xml:id="d198fn2">Two memoranda attached but
                        not printed.</note> request for your approval to proceed with a $15 million
                    loan to the Korean Reconstruction Bank, the major source of development finance
                    for Korean industry. The Bank has helped spur the rapid growth of the
                    manufacturing sector, which increased output by 18% in 1966 and 22% in 1967.</p>
                <p>The Korean Government will increase its own subscription to the Bank by $23
                    million.</p>
                <p>The proposed loan would be the last <gloss target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss> loan to
                    Korea in <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 1968 for a total of $30 million, as
                    against $61 million last year.</p>
                <p>Proceeds from this loan are to be used exclusively to buy machinery, equipment
                    and services in the United States. Treasury agrees that the loan would have a
                    minimum adverse effect on the U.S. balance of payments.</p>
                <pb facs="0457" n="425" xml:id="pg_425"/>
                <p>State also concurs in the loan.</p>
                <p>I recommend that you approve the proposed loan.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">
                            <persName corresp="#p_RWW1">Walt</persName>
                        </hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Approve<note n="3" xml:id="d198fn3">This option is checked.</note>
                    </p>
                    <p>Disapprove</p>
                    <p>Call me</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
